ITEM NO.28               COURT NO.11               SECTION IV-A
               S U P R E M E  C O U R T  O F  I N D I A
                       RECORD OF PROCEEDINGS
SPECIAL LEAVE PETITION (CIVIL) Diary No(s). 14531/2025
[Arising out of impugned final judgment and order dated  23-01-2025
in WA No. 352/2023 (SC-ST) passed by the High Court of Karnataka at
Bengaluru]
SUSHEELAMMA @ SUSHEELA & ANR.                      Petitioner(s)
                                VERSUS
THE STATE OF KARNATAKA & ORS.                      Respondent(s)
(IA No. 149447/2025 - CONDONATION OF DELAY IN REFILING /  CURING
THE DEFECTS, IA No. 149443/2025 - EXEMPTION FROM FILING C/C OF THE
IMPUGNED JUDGMENT, IA No. 149444/2025 - EXEMPTION FROM FILING O.T.)
 
Date : 07-07-2025 This matter was called on for hearing today.
CORAM : 
         HON'BLE MR. JUSTICE SUDHANSHU DHULIA
         HON'BLE MR. JUSTICE JOYMALYA BAGCHI
(PARTIAL COURT WORKING DAYS BENCH)
For Petitioner(s)   M/S.  S-legal Associates, AOR (NP)
                   
For Respondent(s)  
          UPON hearing the counsel the Court made the following
                             O R D E R
In spite of this matter being pass over in the first call,
none appears on behalf of the petitioners in the second call as
well. 
The present petition is dismissed for non-prosecution along
with pending application(s), if any.
(NIRMALA NEGI)                                  (RENU BALA GAMBHIR)
ASTT. REGISTRAR-cum-PS                        ASSISTANT  REGISTRAR
